{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"60a9ed3b-74e5-4ae6-9b6f-0b42e4583fc4","content":"On macOS, the system's **ReportCrash** daemon automatically captures crash reports — no `createdump` needed.\n\n**Crash reports** (`.ips` or `.crash` files) are in:\n\n```\n~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/      # user processes\n/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/       # system processes\n```\n\nFind yours with:\n```bash\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/ | head\n```\n\nYou can also browse them in **Console.app → Crash Reports**.\n\n**For a full core dump** (if you need it for `lldb`):\n\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited        # enable core dumps (disabled by default)\n./MyApp                     # reproduce the crash\nls /cores/                  # core files land here\n```\n\nThen attach with:\n```bash\nlldb ./MyApp -c /cores/core.<pid>\n```\n\nThe `.ips` crash report alone often has enough info (faulting thread, stack trace, signal type) to diagnose the issue without a full core dump.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5396109f-505c-4c84-b660-54c4ef39b8ac","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET application on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to search any codebase.\n\nOn macOS, when an app crashes, the system generates crash reports automatically via ReportCrash. Here's what I know:\n\n1. **macOS Crash Reports** are stored in:\n   - `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (user-level crashes)\n   - `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (system-level crashes)\n\n2. Files are typically named `<process_name>_<date>_<hostname>.ips` (or `.crash` on older macOS versions).\n\n\n3. Console.app provides a graphical way to view these reports, and if you want actual core dumps, they'd go to `/cores/` but you'll need to enable them first with `ulimit -c unlimited` before launching the application since they're disabled by default.","outputTokens":509,"requestId":"419A:7D36C:635C607:6C96227:69F1632F"},"id":"db348c0d-07b1-4067-91ab-96eccce35f3e","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:47:41.704Z","parentId":"6262a299-0f31-415e-a91b-d59506c4e7fa"}
